https://image.tmdb.org/t/p/w500/zVDvqJOxB0A6p0DNTEL5qI6pgFb.jpg Bing Crosby was, without a doubt, the most popular and influential multi-media star of the first half of the twentieth century, pulling audiences in with his intimate, laid-back voice and innate charm. Narrated by Stanley Tucci and directed by Robert Trachtenberg, this film explores the life and legend of this iconic performer, revealing a personality far more complex than the image the public had only thought they'd known. Bing Crosby: Rediscovered
